-- Raiffeisen Names Hameseder as RZB Chairman Replacing Konrad
-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 2012-04-11T15:49:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/raiffeisen-names-hameseder-as-rzb-chairman-replacing-konrad-1-.html
Erwin Hameseder, currently chief
executive officer of Raiffeisenlandesbank NOe-Wien AG, has been
proposed as chairman of  Raiffeisen Zentralbank Oesterreich AG (RZBOPA) ,
to succeed Christian Konrad, who plans to retire this year.  Hameseder will also become head of Raiffeisen Holding NOe-
Wien, the Vienna-based company said in a statement today. Konrad
is proposing that Hameseder be succeeded by Klaus Buchleitner as
CEO of RLB NOe-Wien and as head of Raiffeisen Holding NOe-Wien,
according to the statement. The votes are due to take place at
annual general meetings on May 4.  Raiffeisen Holding owns stakes in 720 companies including
RLB NOe-Wien,  Agrana Beteiligungs AG (AGR) ,  Strabag SE (STR)  and  Do & Co
Restaurants & Catering AG (DOC) , according to its  website .  RZB, which is closely held by eight regional cooperative
lenders including RLB NOe-Wien, is the main shareholder of
 Raiffeisen Bank International AG. (RBI)   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  